My 3 Go to Stretch’s
1️⃣Couch Stretch : helps with hip extension, hip mobility, knee mobility
2️⃣Elevated Pigeon Pose: (only elevated because I can’t do it on the floor 🙃) helps with hip mobility, helps to stretch the glute
3️⃣ Side Bend: helps to lengthen QL and obliques
All of these stretches can be modified. They all can help alleviate low back pain and stiffness. Reminder: you should be able to breathe and stay calm while stretching, if it’s so painful that you aren’t breathing or your face is telling a story, back off. 
#stretch #mobility #hipmobility #fitness

Facts! The funny part is, I wasn’t even using my phone when I fell of the bike.
My sister said I should say that a giant lizard jumped out in front of me and that’s why I fell 😂, but the truth is I couldn’t event tell you how I managed this. I ride in Brooklyn all the time with cars and people everywhere. I guess it’s to quiet here and I got to comfortable. I’m not sure. But it definitely made me work through the uncomfortable. Besides actually hurting myself, I have always wanted to go on long bike rides but I’m always afraid that something will happen. Well now it happened and I’m ok! That’s the point right? Some fear is valid, and having fear isn’t bad thing, except for when it stops us from living.  Obviously I got very lucky and I’m grateful for that. I’m not going to lie that the first time I went on a solo trip and everytime since I’ve been pretty anxious about it. Partially because I hate flying, I’m a creature of habit, and I only make money if i’m at work.
But everytime the plane lands, my anxiety disappears. I love to travel and I want to see the world, so I can’t let my fears stop me.
I got a lot of questions about my solo travel experiences. I just want to say, I’m not an expert, but here’s what I can tell you.
The positives: 
1. you get to do whatever you want (with no differing opinions 
2. You get to move at your own pace
3. You get to spend time with yourself
4. You get to meet new people
—
The negatives:
1. It can be lonely
2. There is no one there to help put sunscreen on your back 😂
3. There is no on there to take your instagram photos
4. You have to be ok with saying “just me” (iykyk)
-
I think most importantly don’t wait for others  or for your fears to go away, do the traveling you want to do.
Do your research, be aware of your surroundings, keep your phone charged, and most importantly have fun! 💙☀️
#travel #solotravel #plussizetravel #dominicanrepublic

Glutes and glute training are the rage, but did you know that training your glutes actually are important and have nothing to do with aesthetics.
1) Strong Glutes help improve your posture and body’s alignment, reminder your glutes are really a part of your “core”, they are a huge part of how are body’s function.
2) Strong Glutes play a huge role in improving athletic performance, this is in any sport or form of movement
3) Strong Glutes can help prevent injury, having a strong posterior chain and that functions well can help prevent injury.
So remember while glute training is all the rage and you see so many posts about ‘how to get glutes like me’ the aesthetics don’t matter if they don’t also aid in function 🦵🦵🦵
-
-
#glutetraining #strengthtraining #gluteworkout #glutes #smarttraining

3 lessons I continue to learn everyday 
1️⃣ Listen to your body, it is telling you what you need to know if you take a moment and listen. It’s so easy to either push to hard or not go hard enough because we never slow down and take a moment to pay attention to the signals we are getting.
2️⃣ You can do more than you think, always!  I’m guilty of thinking I can’t do things or that I won’t be able to do very much. But I remind myself that I’m always capable of 1 more, it may be uncomfortable, but I’m always capable.
3️⃣ It’s ok to miss a workout, this one is hard for me. Me and my type A, Virgo self, have a hard time without some version of structure. Structure and consistency are not only important but they also just keep me sane 😜, but from time to time life happens and you will miss a workout. And sometimes I just have to remind myself that it is ok.
-
-
#fitnessjourney #mobility #parkworkout #outdoorworkout #plussizefitness #lululemonambassador

The shit women don’t talk about…

I’m reposting this from my stories yesterday because I’m clearly not alone. The amount of people that dm’d me telling me their story was unreal.  Im pretty transparent on this app, I don’t have anything to hide. But this has been a topic that have not talked about much because it’s the thing that I’m most insecure about. The thing that has been an issue for me since I was a kid. I’ve spent so much money on laser treatments (money I wish I had back), none of it worked. 
Im posting again because I always want to use this platform to normalize whats clearly normal.  The beauty standards clearly state that woman shouldn’t have facial hair and the amount of money that we all spend on shaving, waxing, laser, electrolysis is astronomical. I’m going to continue to shave because it’s what works best for me, but I’m also going to try my best to not feel so embarrassed by it. I appreciate everyone who shared their story and made me feel less alone ❤️

-I cut myself shaving this morning, I hit my mole and it has been bleeding for hours 😫
I spent my whole morning trying to stop it and I had to give into a band aid. I of course was feeling super self conscious about it. Someone at work (not trying to be mean) of course made a joke and I had a moment of being mortified. I then said that’s exactly what happen. I’m not saying I’m proud, if anything it’s taking so much for me to post this and it’s still bleeding 😐 so im just annoyed. But this is for sure the thing I’m most insecure about and I know I can’t be alone, I know there are so many women that have facial hair that pay so much money each year to try and hide it. Anyway just wanted to send love to anyone else feeling self conscious today. We’ve got this! ❤️
#pcos #facialhair #pcosawareness #normalizenormalbodies

“I don’t run” … I say this all the time.  At some point this became a defense mechanism.  The trauma that I have from running is real.  As a kid I was always slowest, I was not only bullied by my peers but also bullied by the “adults”, the coaches. At different points in my life, I trained incredibly hard to become someone that runs, someone who could keep up. I had some high points, but I never truly enjoyed it and I was never really able to keep up. But at the end of the day, I’m not in gym class anymore. My pace is my pace, and there is no pass or fail. There is just try and do. The truth is that I do run, not regularly, and it’s still not something I love. But I do run. I am capable even at my own pace.
We are all capable, move at your own pace.
I’m going to work on my language, I do run, I can run, but it’s also ok that I don’t love running ❤️😂😝
-
Also shout out to my friends who have always had it right @300poundsandrunning @iamlshauntay @themirnavator
Thank you for always inspiring ❤️

I don’t know if its mercury, lack of awareness and education, or just plain hate and fear.
I’ve been seeing a real backwards trend of “body positivity” “body acceptance” “fat positivity” whatever you want to call it.
I’m seeing it in fashion, I’m seeing it in marketing, and I’m definitely seeing it in fitness.
Pendulums swing and so I shouldn’t be surprised or upset that this swing is happening.  Especially given the state of the whole world and all of the very important issues that are taking place and therefore my acceptance and so many others, isn’t on the list of priorities. 

To My fat friends and my friends that support and don’t hate on bodies of all shapes and sizes, we have to support each other. And there are many ways in which we can do that.

Give a like & comment, follow fat influencers and people that are making change, show up to events they are having, buy the products they are making, share on socials and with friends.

This support equals visibility, this visibility means we show up in-front of all the people who want this pendulum to swing backwards.

Let’s work to move forward, tag people who should be shouted out, tag people who deserve some love, tag brands that are inclusive, tag community’s that are working to make change. 
Let’s show some love ❤️
📸 @aundre

Yesterday @kharveyfit competed in her first sanctioned powerlifting meet. Not only did she get first in her weight class but she also came back from a moment that could have taken her out. One that I know all to well myself. 
I haven’t competed in many years, but coaching is bringing me so much joy.
All of the work I put in, all of the moments I went through are now lessons I get to pass down to my athletes.
1) Respect the Bar
2) Hard work, dedication, and consistency will pay off
3) Do if for you and no one else!
4) The biggest lessons are learned in the hardest moments
5) Have fun!
There are so many more, but these are the ones that stand out the most.
I have a goal to help more people find a love of fitness and lifting, of creating a space for people to feel safe and comfortable doing something that is incredibly uncomfortable and scary.
Who knows if I’ll compete again, but getting to see how happy and excited Keri was at the end of this meet is exactly why I will continue to do what I love ❤️💪❤️💪
-
#powerlifting #1stplace #hardworkpaysoffs #plussizefitness #femalestrengthcoach #strongwomen

The most important days. 
Do you ever just have one of those days where everything feels off. Your clothes don’t fit right, your hair isn’t how you want it to look, your mood is just off. 

I think those are the most important days.

Confidence may come easily to some, but for many it’s hard work.
It took me years to feel confident in myself, my body, in who I am. So it’s no wonder that some days I don’t feel that way. To me these are the most important days because I can prove to myself how strong I’ve become. I can let myself have the feelings but without letting those feeling pull me back under.

On days that I feel off, physically or mentally. I make sure to repeat my mantra. I make sure to remind myself that the feeling is just a feeling. I make sure to take a moment and reset and not let the negative thoughts win.

My current mantra is, I am strong, I am beautiful, I am loved.
What’s yours?
-
#selflove #mantra #mentalhealth
